modules.description: This module encodes QR input data into QR images and writes them as PNG files. It operates on `QRinput.t` values to generate `QRcode.t` structures, which are then rendered into pixel data with specified size, margin, and output path. Use it to generate scannable QR codes from text or binary data, saving them directly to disk as images.

This module manages input data for QR code generation, supporting operations to create and append encoded data chunks. It works with a custom type `t` representing QR input state, along with string-based content and mode specifiers. Concrete use cases include building multi-segment QR codes with different encoding modes like numeric, alphanumeric, or binary.

Encodes text into QR codes with customizable size and margin parameters. Accepts string input and writes the resulting image to a specified file path. Useful for generating scannable QR images directly from textual data.

This module generates QR codes from text or binary data, supporting multiple encoding modes like numeric, alphanumeric, and 8-bit data. It provides functions to construct QR input segments, encode them into QR images, and save the result as PNG files with specified dimensions and margins. Use it to create scannable QR codes for URLs, contact information, or arbitrary binary payloads.
